## 10-Point PR Security Checklist (6 BLOCKING)
1. [BLOCKING] No destructive SQL (DROP TABLE/COLUMN, TRUNCATE, DELETE without WHERE)
2. [BLOCKING] RLS enabled on every new table, policies tested
3. [BLOCKING] Auth checks on every new API route/Edge Function
4. [BLOCKING] No secrets, tokens, or API keys in code
5. [BLOCKING] No force pushes or history rewrites
6. [BLOCKING] User input sanitized before LLM prompt injection
7. Test coverage present for new logic
8. Types match schema (run type generation if schema changed)
9. No duplicate work (check for parallel agent branches)
10. Consistent patterns (matches existing codebase conventions)

## Workflow Engine & Suggestion-Only Policy (BC7 → BC7.1)
Agents execute multi-step work via the workflow engine (`create_workflow` → `advance_workflow` → `complete_step`). As of Apr 25, 2026, agents are **suggestion-only**: `git_operations` has been revoked from developer/researcher RBAC roles. Agents propose changes via `write_workspace_file` + `create_task` (assignee: `cursor-workspace`). David reviews and implements. Step transitions trigger agent wake-ups via `WORKFLOW_WAKE_ENABLED`. Safeguards:
- `expire-stale-workflows.js` — cancels zombie workflows and cascade-cancels blocked dependents
- `post-session.sh` — auto-fails running steps when agent sessions end
- `verify-shipped-output.js` — audits completed steps every 4h for missing output

## Emergency: Agent Merged Bad Code
1. git revert <hash> --no-edit && git push origin dev
2. Close related agent PRs
3. Notify David

## The Rule
NEVER conclude Base Camp "hasn't launched" based on static git analysis. Query the dashboard API or OpenClaw CLI. The system is live — 336+ agent runs, 20/21 agents active (7-day window), 579+ inter-agent messages, 230+ tasks on the board, 133 workflows created, 2700+ GitHub events tracked, 6 marketing channels live.
